HSC Survey Results

Scots Bay Survey # 1 Results from 22/05/2023

Survey Details

4 commercial purse seiners conducted this non-fishing survey on 22/05/2023 starting at 21:00:00.

2 vessels ran the following lines: Morning Star ran one line in the Main Box and all lines in the Eastern Box, Fundy Monarch ran one line in the Main Box and three lines in the North Box, while Brunswick Provider and Sealife II both ran two lines in the Main Box.

There was a plankton tow and replicate conducted by Sealife II.

No tags were applied during this survey.

Since no fish were caught, no samples were obtained for target strength estimation.

Tides Tables

Tide Schedule for Margaretsville NS, Station #315, Source: www.waterlevels.gc.ca

Acoustic Equipment

Each vessel was equipped with a Simrad ES38-18/200-18C combi (2-in-1) transducer prior to the survey that contains a 38kHz split beam and 200 kHz single beam transducer. Data was logged to the computer hard-drive for post-processing. BP and FM were calibrated on 38kHz before the survey, while all NS vessels were uncalibrated.

Survey Results

Main Results

The results are subject to change as DFO will re-evaluate data editing, area estimation and apply a target strength.

Preliminary biomass prediction for Scots Bay using standardized parallel transects is 40,856mt.

Vessel Performance

Speed

Average vessel speed was 8.43. This is above the 8 knot requirement; vessels are urged to slow down to prevent backscatter noise from interfering with the acoustic data.

Distance

More than 2km of distance was cut from the planned lines; vessels are reminded to complete their assigned lines straight and without deviating or cutting corners short.
